ciscoVoiceAnalogIfMIB.name: ciscoVoiceAnalogIfMIB

revisions.description: Extend cvaIfEMCfgSignalType to include fgd(5) and fgd-eana(6)
Extend CvaIfEMCfgEntry to include cvaIfEMCfgAutoGainControl Extend CvaIfEMTimingEntry to include cvaIfEMTimeoutPttXmt cvaIfEMTimeoutPttRcv cvaIfEMTimingDelayVoice add cvaIfEMGroupRev2

Extend cvaIfEMCfgSignalType to include lmr(4) Extend CvaIfEMCfgEntry to include cvaIfEMCfgLmrMCap & cvaIfEMCfgLmrECap Extend CvaIfEMTimingEntry to include cvaIfEMTimingVoiceHangover & cvaIfEMTimeoutLmrTeardown Deprecated cvaIfEMGroup add cvaIfEMGroupRev1 Addition of fxoCama in cvaIfFXOCfgSignalType. Deprecated cvaIfFXOCfgSupDisconnect in favor of cvaIfFXOCfgSupDisconnect2. Add cvaIfMIBCompliance2
Deprecated cvaIfFXOCfgSupDisconnect in favor of cvaIfFXOCfgSupDisconnect2.

Created TC InterfaceDialType. Updated cvaIfEMCfgDialType and cvaIfFXOCfgDialType objects to use this TC InterfaceDialType. Added enumeration 'trunked(3)' to the SYNTAX of cvaIfFXSHookStatus. Added enumeration 'trunked(3)' to the SYNTAX of cvaIfFXOHookStatus.

ciscoVoiceAnalogIfMIB.contactinfo: Cisco Systems Customer Service Postal: 170 W. Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134 USA Tel: +1 800 553-NETS E-mail: cs-voice@cisco.com
ciscoVoiceAnalogIfMIB.description: Analog Voice Interface MIB module. This MIB manages the E&M, FXO, FXS Interfaces in the router.

InterfaceDialType.name: InterfaceDialType
InterfaceDialType.description: Specifies the out dialing type of E&M interface and FXO type interfaces. dtmf - DTMF digit. pulse - pulse. mf - mf digit.

cvaIfCfgTable.name: cvaIfCfgTable
cvaIfCfgTable.description: The Analog Voice Standard Configuration Table. It contains the standard configuration information of the analog telephony interface.

cvaIfCfgEntry.name: cvaIfCfgEntry
cvaIfCfgEntry.description: An entry in the configuration table for each voice analog interface. The entry is created when the voice analog hardware is detected.

cvaIfCfgImpedance.name: cvaIfCfgImpedance
cvaIfCfgImpedance.description: Specifies the terminating impedance of voice analog interfaces. other - none of the following; arbitrary, within limits, for special cases. ohms600Real - 600 Ohms. ohms600Complex - 600 Ohms + 2.16uF ohms900Complex - 900 Ohms + 2.16uF. ohmsComplex1 - complex 1; 220 Ohms + 820 Ohms || 115nF. This impedance is primarily used in Germany. ohmsComplex2 - complex 2; 270 Ohms + 750 Ohms || 150nF. This impedance is primarily used in United Kingdom and Sweden.

cvaIfCfgIntegratedDSP.name: cvaIfCfgIntegratedDSP
cvaIfCfgIntegratedDSP.description: Indicates whether the interface has an integrated Digital Signal processing (DSP) unit.

cvaIfStatusTable.name: cvaIfStatusTable
cvaIfStatusTable.description: The Analog Voice Status Table. It contains general information about the status of Analog Telephony interface including the error statistics.

cvaIfStatusEntry.name: cvaIfStatusEntry
cvaIfStatusEntry.description: An entry in the status table for each Analog voice interface.

cvaIfStatusInfoType.name: cvaIfStatusInfoType
cvaIfStatusInfoType.description: The information transfer services for the current or last call. none - no information transfer service voice - analog voice. g3Fax - Group 3 FAX.

cvaIfMaintenanceMode.name: cvaIfMaintenanceMode
cvaIfMaintenanceMode.description: Indicates the maintenance modes of the Analog voice interface. Managed system +=============+=============================+ | Voice | +===========+ telephony | <=====+ application +===+ CODEC +===end point +=== test IP | (Host) | . +===========+ .(Interface)| equipment backbone +=============+=============================+ . . Host ======>===+ . Compressed <======+ . . . Host ===================>======+ Uncompressed <======================+ . . Interface +========<========================== Compressed +==================================> . . Interface . +===<=============== Uncompressed . +==================> Compress Uncompress Loopback Loopback point point none(1) - the interface is not in maintenance mode. hostCompressedLoopback(2) - Host Compressed Loopback. This mode is set by the managed system to perform the compressed voice loopback test. The voice packet is passed by voice application to the interface associated CODEC. Instead of feeding these into the CODEC for decompression, they are immediately sent back to the voice application as if they had originated locally and been compressed. hostUncompressedLoopback(3) - Host Uncompressed Loopback. This mode is set by the managed system to perform the uncompressed voice loopback test. The voice packet is sent by voice application all the way through the interface associated CODEC and then turned around instead of being sent to the telephony endpoint. ifCompressedLoopback(4) - Interface Compressed Loopback. This mode is set by the managed system to perform the interface uncompressed voice loopback test for the external test equipment that is connected to the voice interface. The voice samples are sent from the test equipment all the way through the interface associated CODEC and then turned around instead of being sent to voice application. ifUncompressedLoopback(5) - Interface Uncompressed Loopback. This mode is set by the managed system to perform the interface uncompressed voice loopback test for the external test equipment that is connected to the voice interface. The voice samples are sent from the test equipment to the interface associated CODEC. Instead of feeding the voice samples into the CODEC for compression, they are immediately sent back to the telephony interface.

cvaIfStatusSignalErrors.name: cvaIfStatusSignalErrors
cvaIfStatusSignalErrors.description: Accumulated number of signaling protocol errors that are detected in the interface since system startup.

cvaIfEMCfgTable.name: cvaIfEMCfgTable
cvaIfEMCfgTable.description: The E&M standard configuration table. It contains the current setting of E&M configurable parameters.

cvaIfEMCfgEntry.name: cvaIfEMCfgEntry
cvaIfEMCfgEntry.description: An entry in the standard configuration table for each E&M tie trunk interface.

cvaIfEMCfgSignalType.name: cvaIfEMCfgSignalType
cvaIfEMCfgSignalType.description: The signaling type of E&M tie trunk interface. winkStart - the calling side seizes the line by going off-hook on its E lead but waits for a short off-hook 'wink' indication on its M lead from the called side before sending address information as DTMF digits. immediateDial - the calling side seizes the line by going off-hook on its E lead and sends sends address information as DTMF digits. delayDial - the calling side seizes the line by going off-hook on its E lead. After a timing interval, the calling side looks at the supervision from the called side. If the supervision is on-hook, the calling side starts sending information as DTMF digits; otherwise, the calling side waits until the called side goes on-hook and then starts sending address information. lmr - the e&m port is used to interface with Land Mobil Radio system. The e-lead and m-lead are not used in the traditional way. fgd - Feature Group D is an access switched services that provides access to Local Exchange Carrier of the public switched network. It is supported in North America only based on E&M wink-start. fgd-eana - Exchange Access North American signalling protocol of Feature Group D.

cvaIfEMCfgOperation.name: cvaIfEMCfgOperation
cvaIfEMCfgOperation.description: Specify the operation of the E&M signal. twoWires - 2-wire operation. fourWires - 4-wire operation.

cvaIfEMCfgType.name: cvaIfEMCfgType
cvaIfEMCfgType.description: Specifies the E&M Lead Signaling type. LEGEND: V = -48V /\/\/ = detector/resister X = normally open relay contact + = normally closed relay contact G = ground SB = Signal Battery SG = Signal Ground typeI - Leads: E (output, relay to ground) M (input, referenced to ground) The tie line equipment (switch/router/etc) generates the E-signal to the PBX type grounding the E-lead. The tie line equipment detects the M-signal by detecting current flow to ground. A common ground must exist between the line equipment and the PBX. PBX | TIE LINE | E: V--/\/\/---|-----X----G | M: V----X-----|---/\/\/--G typeII - Leads: E (output, relay to SG) M (input, referenced to ground) SB (feed for M, connected to -48V) SG (return for E, galvanically isolated from ground) This interface requires no common ground between the equipment, thus avoiding ground loop noise problems. E-signal is generated toward the PBX by connecting it to SG. M-signal is indicated by the PBX connecting it to SB. While this interface does NOT require a common ground, it does have the tendency to inject noise into the audio paths since it is asymmetrical with respect to current flow between devices. PBX | TIE LINE | E: V--/\/\/---|-----X---- | | SG: G----------|---------- | M: ----X-----|---/\/\/--G | | SB: ----------|----------V typeIII - Leads: E (output, relay to ground) M (input, referenced to ground) SB (connected to -48V) SG (connected to ground) This interface operates similar to type I with respect to the E-signal. The M-signal, however, is indicated by the PBX connecting it to SB on assertion, and alternately connecting it to SG during inactivity. Unfortunately, a common ground must be shared between the equipment. PBX | TIE LINE | E: V--/\/\/---|-----X----G | SG: ----------|----------G + | M: ----------|---/\/\/--G X | SB: ----------|----------V typeIV - Leads: E (output, relay to SG) M (input, referenced to -48V) SB (feed for M, connected to ground) SG (return for E, galvanically isolated from ground) This interface is fully symmetrical; it does not require a common ground, does not inject noise into audio paths, and can be connected back to back by swapping E/SG for M/SB. E-signal is indicated to the PBX by connecting it to SG. M-signal is provided by the PBX connecting it to SB. PBX | TIE LINE | E: V--/\/\/---|-----X---- | | SG: G----------|---------- | M: ----------|---/\/\/--V X | SB: ----------|----------G typeV - Leads: E (output, relay to ground) M (input, referenced to -48V) Type V line equipment indicates E-signal to the PBX by grounding the E-lead. The PBX indicates M-signal by grounding the M-lead. This interface does require a common ground, but does allow back to back connections by swapping E for M. This interface is quasi-symmetric in that while the line is up, current flow is more or less equal between the PBX and line equipment. But noise injection is still a problem. PBX | TIE LINE | E: V--/\/\/---|-----X----G | M: G-----X----|---/\/\/--V |

cvaIfEMCfgDialType.name: cvaIfEMCfgDialType
cvaIfEMCfgDialType.description: Specifies the out dialing type of E&M interface.

cvaIfEMCfgLmrMCap.name: cvaIfEMCfgLmrMCap
cvaIfEMCfgLmrMCap.description: The M lead behavior of E&M LMR interface. inact - The m-lead status should be ignored. audio - The m-lead status is used to control generating voice packet. dial - Perform the same audio case except abling to initiate a call when offhook in a idle state.

cvaIfEMCfgLmrECap.name: cvaIfEMCfgLmrECap
cvaIfEMCfgLmrECap.description: The E lead behavior of E&M LMR interface. seize - The e-lead used as seize signal voice - The e-lead status is used to indicate voice packet received or not. inactive -- e-lead is inactive.

cvaIfEMCfgAutoGainControl.name: cvaIfEMCfgAutoGainControl
cvaIfEMCfgAutoGainControl.description: This object is used to enabling/disabling automatic gain control(AGC) on this interface. AGC allows DSP to adjust the input voice volume and avoid rapid voice volume change.

cvaIfEMStatusTable.name: cvaIfEMStatusTable
cvaIfEMStatusTable.description: The E&M interface Table. The table contains the status of the E&M tie trunk interface.

cvaIfEMStatusEntry.name: cvaIfEMStatusEntry
cvaIfEMStatusEntry.description: An entry in the status table for each E&M interface.

cvaIfEMInSeizureActive.name: cvaIfEMInSeizureActive
cvaIfEMInSeizureActive.description: This object contains the incoming seizure state of the E&M interface. If the value is true, then the interface has an incoming trunk seizure active; otherwise, it doesn't.

cvaIfEMOutSeizureActive.name: cvaIfEMOutSeizureActive
cvaIfEMOutSeizureActive.description: This object contains the outgoing seizure state of the E&M interface. If the value is true, then the interface has an outgoing trunk seizure active; otherwise, it doesn't.

cvaIfEMTimingTable.name: cvaIfEMTimingTable
cvaIfEMTimingTable.description: The E&M tie trunk Timing Parameters table. It contains the configuration of the various E&M signaling protocol timing parameters.

cvaIfEMTimingEntry.name: cvaIfEMTimingEntry
cvaIfEMTimingEntry.description: An entry in the E&M Timing Parameters Table for each E&M interface.

cvaIfEMTimingDigitDuration.name: cvaIfEMTimingDigitDuration
cvaIfEMTimingDigitDuration.description: Outgoing DTMF digit duration in milliseconds.

cvaIfEMTimingInterDigitDuration.name: cvaIfEMTimingInterDigitDuration
cvaIfEMTimingInterDigitDuration.description: Outgoing DTMF inter-digit duration in milliseconds.

cvaIfEMTimingPulseRate.name: cvaIfEMTimingPulseRate
cvaIfEMTimingPulseRate.description: Outgoing pulse dialing rate in pulses per second (pps).

cvaIfEMTimingPulseInterDigitDuration.name: cvaIfEMTimingPulseInterDigitDuration
cvaIfEMTimingPulseInterDigitDuration.description: Outgoing Pulse dialing inter-digit timing in milliseconds.

cvaIfEMTimingClearWaitDuration.name: cvaIfEMTimingClearWaitDuration
cvaIfEMTimingClearWaitDuration.description: Time of Inactive seizure signal to declare call cleared.

cvaIfEMTimingMaxWinkWaitDuration.name: cvaIfEMTimingMaxWinkWaitDuration
cvaIfEMTimingMaxWinkWaitDuration.description: Maximum time to wait from the outgoing seizure of the line to the time of sending out a wink-pulse.

cvaIfEMTimingMaxWinkDuration.name: cvaIfEMTimingMaxWinkDuration
cvaIfEMTimingMaxWinkDuration.description: Maximum outgoing wink duration (between the wink-pulse leading edge and trailing edge) for wink start signaling.

cvaIfEMTimingDelayStart.name: cvaIfEMTimingDelayStart
cvaIfEMTimingDelayStart.description: Minimum time to wait from outgoing seizure to out-dialing digits for delay start signaling.

cvaIfEMTimingMaxDelayDuration.name: cvaIfEMTimingMaxDelayDuration
cvaIfEMTimingMaxDelayDuration.description: Maximum time to wait from outgoing seizure to out-dialing digits. If the far end does not allow to send digits after the duration specified in the object, a reorder tone will be sent to the calling party.

cvaIfEMTimingMinDelayPulseWidth.name: cvaIfEMTimingMinDelayPulseWidth
cvaIfEMTimingMinDelayPulseWidth.description: Minimum delay-dial pulse duration for incoming call. If the value of this object is 0, then no delay-dial is sent to the far end for the incoming call.

cvaIfEMTimingVoiceHangover.name: cvaIfEMTimingVoiceHangover
cvaIfEMTimingVoiceHangover.description: The hangover time used to determine the casethere is no more voice packet arrived.

cvaIfEMTimeoutLmrTeardown.name: cvaIfEMTimeoutLmrTeardown
cvaIfEMTimeoutLmrTeardown.description: LMR port tear down timeout. This object is relevant to the waiting time of teardown call on LMR port. if the value of this object is '-1', then the timeout is disable.

cvaIfEMTimeoutPttXmt.name: cvaIfEMTimeoutPttXmt
cvaIfEMTimeoutPttXmt.description: This object signifies LMR port maxinum transmit time. This object is relevant to how long LMR port can continue transmit voice packet without pause.

cvaIfEMTimeoutPttRcv.name: cvaIfEMTimeoutPttRcv
cvaIfEMTimeoutPttRcv.description: This object signifies LMR port maxinum receive time. This object is relevant to how long LMR port can continue receive voice packet without pause.

cvaIfEMTimingDelayVoice.name: cvaIfEMTimingDelayVoice
cvaIfEMTimingDelayVoice.description: This object is relevant to how long DSP will delay sending the voice packet to the LMR port.

cvaIfFXOCfgTable.name: cvaIfFXOCfgTable
cvaIfFXOCfgTable.description: The FXO standard configuration table. It contains FXO configuration parameters, one entry per FXO interface. The configuration information of this table is set by hardware with its default setting or CLI during the hardware installation time.

cvaIfFXOCfgEntry.name: cvaIfFXOCfgEntry
cvaIfFXOCfgEntry.description: An entry in the standard configuration table for each FXO interface.

cvaIfFXOCfgSignalType.name: cvaIfFXOCfgSignalType
cvaIfFXOCfgSignalType.description: the signaling type of FXO interface. fxoLoopStart - loop start. fxoGroundStart - ground start. fxoCama - cama.

cvaIfFXOCfgNumberRings.name: cvaIfFXOCfgNumberRings
cvaIfFXOCfgNumberRings.description: The number of rings detected before closing loop.

cvaIfFXOCfgSupDisconnect.name: cvaIfFXOCfgSupDisconnect
cvaIfFXOCfgSupDisconnect.description: Specifies whether a supervisory disconnect signal (CPC) will be presented to the interface when the connected party at the interface hangs up.

cvaIfFXOCfgDialType.name: cvaIfFXOCfgDialType
cvaIfFXOCfgDialType.description: Specifies the out dialing type of FXO interface.

cvaIfFXOCfgSupDisconnect2.name: cvaIfFXOCfgSupDisconnect2
cvaIfFXOCfgSupDisconnect2.description: Specifies the type of supervisory disconnect signal (CPC) to be presented to the interface when the connected party at the interface hangs up. signal - power denial recognition anytone - tone detection of all call progressing tones dualtoneMidcall - tone detection to operate throughout the call duration dualtonePreconnect - tone detection to operate only during call setup

cvaIfFXOStatusTable.name: cvaIfFXOStatusTable
cvaIfFXOStatusTable.description: The Foreign Exchange Office (FXO) interface Status Table. It contains hook status, ring detection and other states of the interface.

cvaIfFXOStatusEntry.name: cvaIfFXOStatusEntry
cvaIfFXOStatusEntry.description: An entry in the status table for each FXO interface.

cvaIfFXOHookStatus.name: cvaIfFXOHookStatus
cvaIfFXOHookStatus.description: This object contains the hook status of FXO interface. onHook - Present the onHook to the connected equipment. offHook - Present the offHook to the connected equipment. trunked - Present the trunk to the connected equipment.

cvaIfFXORingDetect.name: cvaIfFXORingDetect
cvaIfFXORingDetect.description: This object contains the ring detect indication. If the value is true, then the interface detects ring from PBX or CO; otherwise, it doesn't.

cvaIfFXORingGround.name: cvaIfFXORingGround
cvaIfFXORingGround.description: This object contains the incoming ring ground indication. It is only valid when the cvaIfFXOCfgSignalType is fxoGroundStart. If the object is true, then the interface is presenting a ring ground to the connected equipment; otherwise, it doesn't.

cvaIfFXOTipGround.name: cvaIfFXOTipGround
cvaIfFXOTipGround.description: This object contains the incoming tip ground indication. It is only valid when the cvaIfFXOCfgSignalType is fxoGroundStart. If the object is true, then the interface is detecting a tip ground at the interface; otherwise, it doesn't.

cvaIfFXOTimingTable.name: cvaIfFXOTimingTable
cvaIfFXOTimingTable.description: The FXO interface Timing Parameters table. It contains the configuration of the various FXO signaling protocol timing parameters.

cvaIfFXOTimingEntry.name: cvaIfFXOTimingEntry
cvaIfFXOTimingEntry.description: An entry in the FXO Timing Parameters Table for each FXO interface.

cvaIfFXOTimingDigitDuration.name: cvaIfFXOTimingDigitDuration
cvaIfFXOTimingDigitDuration.description: Outgoing DTMF digit duration in milliseconds.

cvaIfFXOTimingInterDigitDuration.name: cvaIfFXOTimingInterDigitDuration
cvaIfFXOTimingInterDigitDuration.description: Outgoing DTMF inter-digit duration in milliseconds.

cvaIfFXOTimingPulseRate.name: cvaIfFXOTimingPulseRate
cvaIfFXOTimingPulseRate.description: Outgoing pulse dialing rate in pulses per second (pps).

cvaIfFXOTimingPulseInterDigitDuration.name: cvaIfFXOTimingPulseInterDigitDuration
cvaIfFXOTimingPulseInterDigitDuration.description: Outgoing pulse dialing inter-digit timing in milliseconds.

cvaIfFXSCfgTable.name: cvaIfFXSCfgTable
cvaIfFXSCfgTable.description: The FXS standard configuration table. It contains FXS configuration parameters, one entry per FXS interface. The configuration information of this table is set by hardware with its default setting or CLI during the hardware installation time.

cvaIfFXSCfgEntry.name: cvaIfFXSCfgEntry
cvaIfFXSCfgEntry.description: An entry in the standard configuration table for each FXS interface.

cvaIfFXSCfgSignalType.name: cvaIfFXSCfgSignalType
cvaIfFXSCfgSignalType.description: the signaling type of FXS interface. fxsLoopStart - loop start. fxsGroundStart - ground start.

cvaIfFXSRingFrequency.name: cvaIfFXSRingFrequency
cvaIfFXSRingFrequency.description: the ring frequency to be used in the FXS interface. ringFrequency25 - ring frequency 25 Hertz. ringFrequency50 - ring frequency 50 Hertz. ringFrequency20 - ring frequency 20 Hertz. ringFrequency30 - ring frequency 30 Hertz.

cvaIfFXSStatusTable.name: cvaIfFXSStatusTable
cvaIfFXSStatusTable.description: The Foreign Exchange Station (FXS) interface Status Table. It contains hook status, ring active and other states of the interface.

cvaIfFXSStatusEntry.name: cvaIfFXSStatusEntry
cvaIfFXSStatusEntry.description: An entry in the status table for each FXS interface.

cvaIfFXSHookStatus.name: cvaIfFXSHookStatus
cvaIfFXSHookStatus.description: This object contains the hook status of FXS interface. onHook - the connected equipment(e.g., phone) is onHook. offHook - the connected equipment is offHook. trunked - the connected equipment is trunked.

cvaIfFXSRingActive.name: cvaIfFXSRingActive
cvaIfFXSRingActive.description: This object contains the outgoing ring active indication. If the object value is true, then the interface is currently generating ring out to the Key Telephone System (KTS) or Plain Old Telephone (POT); otherwise, it doesn't.

cvaIfFXSRingGround.name: cvaIfFXSRingGround
cvaIfFXSRingGround.description: This object contains the incoming ring ground indication. It is only valid when the cvaIfFXSCfgSignalType is fxsGroundStart. If the object is true, then the interface is presenting a ring ground to the connected equipment; otherwise, it doesn't.

cvaIfFXSTipGround.name: cvaIfFXSTipGround
cvaIfFXSTipGround.description: This object contains the incoming tip ground indication. It is only valid when the cvaIfFXSCfgSignalType is fxsGroundStart. If the object is true, then the interface is detecting a tip ground at the interface; otherwise, it doesn't.

cvaIfFXSTimingTable.name: cvaIfFXSTimingTable
cvaIfFXSTimingTable.description: The FXS interface Timing Parameters table. It contains the configuration of the various FXS signaling protocol timing parameters.

cvaIfFXSTimingEntry.name: cvaIfFXSTimingEntry
cvaIfFXSTimingEntry.description: An entry in the FXS Timing Parameters Table for each FXS interface.

cvaIfFXSTimingDigitDuration.name: cvaIfFXSTimingDigitDuration
cvaIfFXSTimingDigitDuration.description: Outgoing DTMF digit duration in milliseconds.

cvaIfFXSTimingInterDigitDuration.name: cvaIfFXSTimingInterDigitDuration
cvaIfFXSTimingInterDigitDuration.description: Outgoing DTMF inter-digit duration in milliseconds.

cvaIfMIBCompliance.name: cvaIfMIBCompliance
cvaIfMIBCompliance.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement the Cisco Analog Voice interface MIB

cvaIfMIBCompliance2.name: cvaIfMIBCompliance2
cvaIfMIBCompliance2.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement the Cisco Analog Voice interface MIB

cvaIfMIBCompliance3.name: cvaIfMIBCompliance3
cvaIfMIBCompliance3.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement the Cisco Analog Voice interface MIB

cvaIfGeneralGroup.name: cvaIfGeneralGroup
cvaIfGeneralGroup.description: The collection of objects providing general information about the Cisco Analog Voice interfaces.

cvaIfEMGroup.name: cvaIfEMGroup
cvaIfEMGroup.description: The collection of objects providing information about the Cisco E&M trunk interface.

cvaIfFXOGroup.name: cvaIfFXOGroup
cvaIfFXOGroup.description: The collection of objects providing information about the Cisco FXO interface.

cvaIfFXSGroup.name: cvaIfFXSGroup
cvaIfFXSGroup.description: The collection of objects providing information about the Cisco FXS interface.

cvaIfFXOGroup2.name: cvaIfFXOGroup2
cvaIfFXOGroup2.description: The collection of objects providing information about the Cisco FXO interface.

cvaIfEMGroupRev1.name: cvaIfEMGroupRev1
cvaIfEMGroupRev1.description: The collection of objects providing information about the Cisco E&M trunk interface.

cvaIfEMGroupRev2.name: cvaIfEMGroupRev2
cvaIfEMGroupRev2.description: The collection of objects providing information about the Cisco E&M trunk interface.
